master.title: Preludio Tema Variazioni Canzona
master.notes:
This album was a collaboration between Osanna and well-known movie soundtrack composer [url=http://www.discogs.com/artist/Luis+Bacalov?anv=Luis+Enriquez+Bacalov]Luis Bacalov[/url], one of three such "rock meets symphonic works" conceived by Bacalov.

The result was the original movie soundtrack to [a2167096]'s classic polizziottescho movie 'Milano Calibro 9' (aka 'Caliber 9'/'Milano Caliber 9'/'The Contract'), where the initial torture scene was "an inspiration" for [a258993]' 1992 'Reservoir Dogs'. The album, however, differs from the OST, where some of Osanna's rock music (recorded "live" to a screening of the movie in Rome) was culled from the soundtrack, which was later re-recorded in Milan.

Luis Bacalov (as Luis Enriquez Bacalov) had already collaborated with The New Trolls on the soundtrack to Maurizio Lucidi's 1971 'La vittima designata' ('The Designated Victim'), with [a1473768], and the result, [m10420], had been such a success that Osanna's record company, [l95714], prompted Osanna and Bacalov to work together.

The third in this trilogy was [m25451] (1973) that wasn't a movie soundtrack.
